cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR 

The paper deals with video person re-identification, which is a computer vision problem related to tracking and recognizing individuals across multiple cameras. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper proposes a novel network architecture to handle partial occlusion, which involves predicting the appearance of occluded body parts using spatial and temporal information. This suggests that the paper could also be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.LG (Machine Learning), which deal with video analysis and deep learning, respectively. Additionally, the paper involves designing a framework for video re-ID that is robust to partial occlusion, which could be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), which deal with developing intelligent systems and ensuring their security, respectively.
